1. STORAGE
   Raw heap pointer (int* arr) — mimics array using pointer arithmetic
   new int[cap] allocates, delete[] arr frees it

2. GROWTH STRATEGY
   When full (sz == cap) — double the capacity
   Allocate new block → copy old data → free old block → point to new
   This gives O(1) amortized push_back

3. BOUNDS SAFETY
   operator[] throws out_of_range for invalid index
   pop_back throws if empty

4. CONST CORRECTNESS
   Getters marked const — safe to call on const references
   operator[] returns reference — enables da[i] = value syntax
